node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Pnwonderland on August 11, 2021 tagging @pelicanbrewing, and @trailkeepersoforegon. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Our friends at @PelicanBrewingCompany are celebrating the release of their new beer, Head Out Hefeweizen, by giving back to our PNW trails. We are excited to work with Pelican Brewing as they sponsor a series @TrailkeepersOfOregon projects dedicated to maintaining and restoring trails all along the North Coast ensuring that these trails can continue to be enjoyed by all.
 
You can join in the action and sign up for a Pelican Sponsored Trailkeepers of Oregon Trail Party or Adventure Vacation. Reward yourself after a day on the trails with Pelican's new light and refreshing wheat ale, Head Out Hefe. This American-Style Hefeweizen is loaded with bright, floral character and melon-like hop aroma with a full-bodied finish. Dive into the light malt sweetness and juicy hop character of this Pacific Northwest inspired beer.
 
Pick up a 6-pack of Head Out Hefeweizen to enjoy after your next adventure. Cheers friends 🍻
